title: Game Recap: Nets 125, Warriors 99
description: Kevin Durant recorded 22 points (7-16 FG), five rebounds and three assists in his Nets debut as they defeated the Warriors, 125-99. Kyrie Irving added 26 points, four rebounds and four assists for the Nets in the victory, while Stephen Curry tallied 20 points, four rebounds and 10 assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. Additionally for the Warriors, James Wiseman, the No.2 overall pick in the 2020 NBA Draft out of the University of Memphis, recorded 19 points and six rebounds in his NBA debut. The Nets improve to 1-0 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 0-1.

description: Led by Paul Georges 33 points (13-18 FG), the Clippers defeated the Lakers, 116-109. Additionally for the Clippers, Kawhi Leonard recorded 26 points in the victory, while LeBron James tallied a team-high 22 points, along with five rebounds and five assists for the Lakers in the losing effort.
